    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>NAPSTER USE QUADRUPLED IN 5 MONTHS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Susan Stellin</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Stellin, Susan</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Media Metrix says number of people using Napster music file-sharing application reached 4.9 million US home users in July, compared with 1.1 million in February; graph (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The number of people using the Napster music file-sharing application reached 4.9 million United States home users in July, according to Media Metrix. That compares with 1.1 million in February, the first month the Internet audience measurement service tracked use of the Napster application. Those numbers came before the service gained notoriety because of litigation over its use as a means to trade copyrighted music files. Napster use also grew steeply among those at work, Media Metrix found.</p>
        <p>Susan Stellin</p>
      </block>
